         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">National Herbarium ¶ Melbourne, 16/1/97 ¶ Dear Miss King ¶  ¶ I have much pleasure in forwarding to you herewith the desired sketches of Boronia pinnata and B. floribunda. I regret that I have not suf...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">97.01.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Georg Luehmann to Georgina King</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Museum of Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">get details from King letters.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>National Herbarium</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 16/1/97</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Miss King</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have much pleasure in forwarding to you herewith the desired sketches of Boronia pinnata and B. floribunda. I regret that I have not sufficient artistic skill to send you a proper drawing. Is it not remarkable that Dr. Woolls never noticed B. floribunda? There is no specimen in out herbarium from him, but we have it from Mrs Rowan (who painted the Australian flowers), from Botany Bay collected by Baron Von Mueller 40 eyars ago, and a specimen from Middle Harbour without the collector's name, as well as several of Sieber's original plants. You would much oblige by sending me some fruiting specimens of this plant.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also G. Luehmann to G. King, 29 January 1897.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. G. Luehmann</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Boronia floribunda, Sieber. Flower seen from above, the stamens spread out flat.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The stamens opposite the petals have short filaments and smaller anthers; all the anthers bear pollen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Style quite short; Stigma very large, globular.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Boronia pinnata, Smith</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Flower seen from above, the stamens spread out flat.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Stamens all equal.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Style rather long;</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Stigma quite small</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">NB. The hairiness of the stamens is not a distinctive character; some of our specimens have them almost or not quite glabrous, others very woolly</p>
         </div>
